SIMPLE: mizzle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mizzle
<hw>Miz"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Mizzled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mizzling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Misle</er>, and cf. <er>Mistle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To rain
in very fine drops; to drizzle.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To take one's self off; to go.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As long as George the Fourth could reign, he reigned,⟦br⟧
And then he <qex>mizzled</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Epigram, quoted by
Wright.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mizzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mizzle
<hw>Miz"zle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Mist; fine rain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mizzy</ent>⟦br⟧
